  "reference": "All PDF/CDF literals are compared against the R 'copula' package (per the C# test class remarks). Tail dependence closed form: lambda_U = lambda_L = 0 (the Normal copula has no tail dependence, unlike the elliptical Student's t copula).",
  "note": "data1/data2 are the SAME 100-element arrays Test_StudentTCopula.cs uses (student_t_copula.json), byte-identical against the upstream test source. data1_pp/data2_pp are the plotting positions (rank/(n+1), via Statistics.RanksInPlace; this dataset has no ties) precomputed here to keep the mpl fit runner thin -- see fixtures/README.md. cdf/cdf_asymmetric cases carry both the upstream 1e-2 literal AND a curated 1e-8 companion assertion for the same (rho, u, v) -- the copula CDF delegates to MultivariateNormal::bivariate_cdf, a deterministic (non-seeded) Drezner/Genz routine, so a tight companion turns silent drift into a loud failure. Companions are 'source': 'curated via oracle_emitter --dump'.",
